<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Kettler</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                1895</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 77.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 13th ultimo, in which you suggest that the
                            decision reached by this Government on the subject of sending their
                            families to join the captive Samoans at Jaluit, as expressed in a letter
                            of the Secretary of State of February 16 last, be reconsidered.</p>
                        <p>In reply I beg to say that I shall avail myself of the earliest
                            practicable opportunity to take up the matter, and meanwhile beg to
                            renew to you, sir, the assurances of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>